Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe Raider’s Unit of the Delta State Police Command busted an 80-year-old man who sells bullets to hoodlums in the Kokori community of Ethiope LGA.
Pa Omoraka James eventually yielded a cache of 114 rounds of live cartridges.
The Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe confirmed the report in a statement.
“The suspect’s premises were raided by the Command Raider’s Unit on the strength of an information received that he deals in Cartridges, sells to hoodlums which they use in carrying out various nefarious activities.”
